data.output: One snowy evening, I set off in my mini cooper to my grandparents house, the journey was around 2 hours in length, about half way through i needed to stop to get some fuel. I had a strange loss of my senses and when I got to the pump i had forgotten whether the car took petrol or diesel, in my moment of madness i filled up the car with the wrong type of fuel! I sadly didn't realise until a few minutes into my journey after setting off ahain

since i was 5 years old i have been collecting stamps in a lovely leather bound book, each year i add to my collection with various limited addition stamps. My mother and I love to look through the book at christmas time and see what different images and stamps have been collected. Sometimes for very special family members birthdays I select a stamp from my collection and i use to it send a letter. I like to choose and envelope colour which really sets off the design of the stamp and i hope very much that the recipient is appreciative of the choice and enjoys opening the special letter.

My uncle decided to donate his organs when he died, which was a very noble thing to do. Sadly on Janurary 7th he fell off his bike and passed away. However many of his organs were able to be donated and his lovely young apprentice who worked in his shop, the Empire of Sweets needed a lung transplant and was able to benefit from my uncles donation. We were a little worried that in order to comply for my uncles lung the shop assistant would not match certain criteria but fortunately he did and all was well.

In the dark gloom of the winter morning, Lisa looked at her payment for the 5 foot teddy bear she had bought last night whilst extremely intoxicated and wondered what on earth she was thinking. Sometimes she felt there was no point in her sad lonely life and whether any one cared she was here. Did she even exist at all?
